This was a conceptual design task for a Binary Classifier. Unlike regression, the goal here is to put data into "buckets" (Spam vs. Not Spam).

💡 System Design
Features (Inputs):

Keywords (e.g., "Free," "Winner," "Urgent").

The sender's domain reputation.

Number of links in the email body.

All-caps subject lines.

Data Needed: Thousands of emails labeled "Spam" or "Ham" (normal) to teach the model patterns.

Possible Mistakes:

False Positive (The worst mistake): Marking an important job offer as Spam.

False Negative: Letting a phishing email into the main Inbox.

Binary Classification: Learned to distinguish between $Y=1$ (Spam) and $Y=0$ (Not Spam) based on feature patterns.
Error Analysis: Understood the critical real-world difference between False Positives and False Negatives.
